<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1540,1783]" pageId="15" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1685,1711]" pageId="15" pageNumber="92">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species may have been misidentified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[842,1044,1685,1711]" pageId="15" pageNumber="92" pagination="55 - 112" refId="ref16691" refString="Mortensen, T. (1940) Echinoderms from the Iranian Gulf. Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea, and Echinoidea. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part 2, 55 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1940">Mortensen (1940)</bibRefCitation>
and confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peyghan et al. 2018)" authorityName="Peyghan" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Peyghan" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="15" pageNumber="92" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="venusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="92">Ophiothela venusta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peyghan, S. &amp; Doustshenas, B. &amp; Nabavi, M. B. &amp; Rounagh, M. T. &amp; Larki, A. A. &amp; Stohr, S." box="[226,455,1721,1747]" pageId="15" pageNumber="92" pagination="425 - 435" refId="ref17581" refString="Peyghan, S., Doustshenas, B., Nabavi, M. B., Rounagh, M. T., Larki, A. A. &amp; Stohr, S. (2018) New records of the brittle stars Ophiothela venusta and Ophiactis modesta (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the northern Persian Gulf, with morphological details. Zootaxa, 4527 (3), 425 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4527.3.11" type="journal article" year="2018">
Peyghan 
<emphasis box="[331,388,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="92">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It has not been found since 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[780,1000,1721,1747]" pageId="15" pageNumber="92" pagination="55 - 112" refId="ref16691" refString="Mortensen, T. (1940) Echinoderms from the Iranian Gulf. Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea, and Echinoidea. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part 2, 55 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1940">Mortensen’s (1940)</bibRefCitation>
record and it is therefore unclear if the species occurs in the study area.
</paragraph>
